law.text:
The 24 soil conservation districts are established and continued with boundaries corresponding to county boundaries, except for Frederick County, and include all land and water and incorporated areas, as follows:
Allegany Soil Conservation District;
Anne Arundel Soil Conservation District;
Baltimore County Soil Conservation District;
Calvert Soil Conservation District;
Caroline Soil Conservation District;
Carroll Soil Conservation District;
Cecil Soil Conservation District;
Charles Soil Conservation District;
Dorchester Soil Conservation District;
Garrett Soil Conservation District;
Harford Soil Conservation District;
Howard Soil Conservation District;
Kent Soil Conservation District;
Montgomery Soil Conservation District;
Prince George's Soil Conservation District;
Queen Anne's Soil Conservation District;
St. Mary's Soil Conservation District;
Somerset Soil Conservation District;
Talbot Soil Conservation District;
Washington County Soil Conservation District;
Wicomico Soil Conservation District;
Worcester Soil Conservation District;
Catoctin Soil Conservation District within the area of Frederick County bounded by the Washington-Frederick County line, the Potomac River, and the eastern and northern boundaries of the Catoctin Creek watershed; and
The Frederick Soil Conservation District comprising the balance of Frederick County land and water area.
